SECTION 2 — COMMERCIAL USE (Requires Agreement)

"Commercial use" means any use where you or your organization directly or
indirectly receive financial benefit, including but not limited to:

  • Offering PagedIn (or a derivative) as a paid product or service
  • Using PagedIn as part of a SaaS, platform, or subscription offering
  • Selling access, features, or exports powered by this software
  • White-labeling or rebranding this software for profit
  • Using this software to generate revenue through ads, leads, or referrals

If you intend to use this software commercially, you must:

  1. Contact the author to obtain a written commercial license
  2. Agree to a revenue share of no less than 15% of gross revenue
     directly attributable to this software
  3. Provide quarterly revenue reports upon request

Unauthorized commercial use is a violation of this license and may be
subject to legal action under applicable copyright law.

To inquire about a commercial license, open an issue or contact via:
https://github.com/plasmacat420/pagedIn

